description:
A ZnO/Ag/ZnO film with 2D periodic apertures can have a high visible transmittance and low emittances in atmospheric windows for visible-infrared compatible camouflage and a high transmittance in 5~8  &mu; m for heat dissipation by radiation. This following protocol details the fabrication process of such a photonic structure based on photolithography technology. Also described are the related challenges and troubleshooting steps. 

 &nbsp; 

 For complete information on the generation and use of this protocol, please refer to Dang et al., (2021).

